    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>5-6 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and your <strong>fish sauce </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add a squeeze of your <strong>lime juice</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>prik nam pla</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> finely</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>cooled rice</strong>, your <strong>crab meat </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until everything is combined</p><p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the <strong>egg[s]</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style crab & egg fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>prik nam pla </strong>to your <strong>Thai-style crab fried rice </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style crab & egg fried rice with prik nam pla</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-crab-and-egg-fried-cauliflower-rice-with-prik-nam-pla/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve your<strong> Thai-style crab & egg fried cauliflower rice with prik nam pla </strong>with the <strong>sliced cucumber </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, a <strong>lime wedge </strong>and your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
